I don't know how this place stays in business.
They have seating for 12 people in the whole entire restaurant.
And their prices are very reasonable (~$14).
That being said, I love coming here.
The place is small, intimate, quaint, and rustic.
The food is fresh, local, and most importantly delicious.
Overall, a good place for a quiet date with good conversation.
Also, the food is not into whatever the season's overhyped foodstuff might be (no quinoa, mission figs, coffee-infused reductions, etc), which I like.

